[
    {
        "type": "H1",
        "text": "PDF INFO & TEST FILE",
        "items": [
            {
                "type": "H2",
                "text": "DOWNLOADING PDF FILES IN A WEB BROWSER",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "type": "H3",
                        "text": "Windows 95 Users",
                        "items": [
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "To download the file directly from within Windows 95 using their Internet Explorer, right click on",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "the hotlink and a pop-up menu will appear. Select the \"Save Target As...\" menu item and then you",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "will be asked to identify a destination for the file on you local hard drive. When the file is fully",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "downloaded, open it in the Acrobat Reader or Exchange program. If you want to view it within",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "your browser--left click on the hot link.",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "Figure 1. Windows 95 Pop-Up Menu with Right Click",
                                "items": []
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "H3",
                        "text": "Macintosh Users",
                        "items": [
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "The same general rules and limitations exist for Macintosh users as have been described above. To",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "download the file to the hard drive, click and hold the mouse button down until a pop-up window",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "appears. Select \"Download Link to Disk\" (MS Explorer 4) or similar menu item, and then choose",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "the destination for the file.",
                                "items": []
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "H1",
        "text": "PDF INFO & TEST FILE",
        "items": [
            {
                "type": "H2",
                "text": "HOW TO USE PDF FILES ON THE INTERNET",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "type": "H3",
                        "text": "Viewing PDF Files On-Line",
                        "items": [
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "It is possible to \"download\" PDF files within your Internet browser using the Adobe Acrobat PDF",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "Viewer plug-in for browsers. If you have an Acrobat plug-in installed, clicking on the PDF hot link",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "will automatically start downloading the file and will show you the first page as soon as it is ready.",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "The Acrobat plug-in will display the first page of the document as soon as it is downloaded; that",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "usually takes several seconds to a minute--depending on the quality and speed of your network",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "connection.",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "The files must be navigated and printed using the Acrobat PDF Viewer's icons and not the",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "browser's menu items. The PDF document MUST be printed using the Acrobat Viewers print icon",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "on the upper left corner of the viewer. If the browser's print menu is used, the document may not",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "print clearly, or not print at all..",
                                "items": []
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "H3",
                        "text": "Viewing PDF Files Off-Line",
                        "items": [
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "The best place to view and use PDF file is off-line. While viewing PDF files on-line is a great",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "feature, it does limit some user interface options and is somewhat impractical for large PDF files",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "on the Internet. It may be wiser to download the file for with the Adobe's Acrobat Reader or",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "Acrobat Exchange applications. The benefit of this is each of these applications allows for faster",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "navigation, use of the search function and index services if the file is included in a detached index.",
                                "items": []
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "H3",
                        "text": "Downloading Limitations of the Internet",
                        "items": [
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "It appears that some service providers place limits on the size of files that they will allow their users",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "to attach to e-mail (usually less than 1 megabyte), or download directly. While the PDF version of",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "a document may appear to be a large file compared to many HTML and graphic files, the PDF file",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "is frequently one-half to one-tenth the size of the parent files! The collection of parent resources",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "would be more difficult to download and would not provide the high level of services available in",
                                "items": []
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "",
                                "text": "the Acrobat PDF format.",
                                "items": []
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "type": "H2",
                "text": "PRINTING PDF FILES",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "The Acrobat Reader is capable of printing to a variety of printer types, including PostScript, HPGL",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "and PCL, without any additional software. Choosing the \"Print...\" menu item in Acrobat will call",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "up the standard print dialog box found on your system. In general, choose \"Shrink to Fit\" option to",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "allow the PDF page images to fit on your paper. There is no required \"paper size\" for a PDF file",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "and it is common for the contents of a PDF file be used as virtual slide show in a landscape format.",
                        "items": []
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "H1",
        "text": "PDF INFO & TEST FILE",
        "items": [
            {
                "type": "H2",
                "text": "SOMETHING FOR FREE!",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "The PDF (Portable Document Format) requires a special stand-alone application, or plug-in for",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "your Web browser to view PDF documents. The basic software is available free from the Adobe",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "Corporation. The free Adobe(R) Acrobat(R) Reader allows you to view, navigate, and print PDF",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "files across all major computing platforms. Acrobat Reader is the free viewing companion to",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "Adobe Acrobat 3.0 and to Acrobat Capture(R) software. All links to PDF files have a icon beside",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "them or \"(PDF)\" in the text link.",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "If you do not have Adobe(R) Acrobat(R) Reader software, it is available free from Adobe Inc. by",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "clicking the Get Acrobat Reader at “http://www.adobe.com/prodindex/acrobat/readstep.html”.",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "A more sophisticated version of this software package called Adobe Acrobat provides the software",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "tools for the creation, basic editing and indexing of PDF files. It is available as a commercially sold",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "product from Adobe. The commercial product is available through most software retailers.",
                        "items": []
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "type": "H2",
                "text": "WHY I USE PDF FILES",
                "items": [
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "I frequently get inquires about our use of PDF files on my Web site. I use them for several",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "reasons:",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "• I can deliver information with higher quality graphics and page formatting.",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "• PDF files can be electronically indexed and searched quickly.",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "• They are compact in size compared to other forms of electronic documents of comparable",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "quality.",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "• I can create high quality documents more easily than using HTML (Hypertext Mark-up",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "Language). Information on Web will frequently have graphics with much lower resolutions",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "than ones in our PDF files.",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "• They can be used with the same predictable results on five computer platforms and operat-",
                        "items": []
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "",
                        "text": "ing systems. (UNIX, Windows 3.1, 95, 98 & NT, Macintosh)",
                        "items": []
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
]